== Obtaining Relics ==
* '''Relics''' can be obtained from a variety of sources including {{2|Elites}}, {{2|Chests}}, the {{2|Merchant}}, or using the {{R|Shovel||2}} at {{2|Rest Sites}}.
* {{QueryLink|Relics|rarity:Ancient|Ancient Relics|2}} are only offered by {{2|Ancients}} at the beginning of each {{2|Acts|Act}}.
* {{QueryLink|Relics|rarity:Shop|Shop Relics|2}} are only obtainable from the [[StS2:Merchant|Merchant]]. The third slot in the Merchant's relic offers is always stocked with a {{QueryLink|Relics|rarity:Shop|Shop Relic|2}}. There are 30 shop relics. Each character has 1 shop relic that is exclusive to them.
* {{QueryLink|Relics|rarity:Event|Event Relics|2}} are obtained through {{2|Events}} and cannot be obtained by any other means.
* {{QueryLink|Relics|rarity:Special|Special Relics|2}} '''only''' include the {{R|Circlet||2}} which is obtained by collecting or encountering every other relic available in a run. (Relics can only be encountered once in a run)

== Spawn Restrictions ==
